## CRITICAL: Folder structure
Keep all data-related logic isolated so the app can be updated without data loss:

```
/client ← React frontend
/server
/routes ← one file per resource (members, events, messages, etc.)
/controllers ← business logic, separate from routes
/models ← SQL query functions (no ORM)
/middleware ← auth.js (JWT verification + role check)
/uploads ← local file storage (gitignored)
db.js ← single PostgreSQL pool export
whatsapp.js ← WhatsApp session management only
index.js ← Express app entry point
/db
schema.sql ← ALL table definitions here, run once manually
seed.sql ← Super admin seed data only
.env.example ← template with all required env vars
```

**Never hard-code data. Never drop or recreate tables in app code. Schema changes go in /db/migrations/ as numbered files.**

